{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3acadd9a-a0ca-4e9e-88e5-b02ea6aeef6a","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your .NET crash dump. A few things to note:\n\n1. **The `dump-collect` skill** I have available is for *collecting* dumps, not analyzing them.\n2. For **analysis**, the typical tools are:\n   - **`dotnet-dump analyze`** — cross-platform, great for managed exceptions, threads, heap\n   - **`lldb` + SOS** (Linux) or **WinDbg** (Windows)\n\nHere are the key commands to run once you load the dump:\n\n```bash\n# Install the tool if needed\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n\n# Open the dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n\n# Inside the analyzer, try these commands:\n> pe                          # Print last exception (often the crash cause)\n> clrstack                    # Managed call stack of current thread\n> clrthreads                  # List all managed threads\n> dumpheap -stat              # Heap summary\n> setthread <id> && clrstack  # Stack for a specific thread\n```\n\n**Common root causes to look for:**\n- `pe` shows an unhandled exception with stack trace\n- `clrstack` on the faulting thread reveals the crashing method\n- `StackOverflowException` or `OutOfMemoryException` in thread stacks\n\nWould you like me to walk you through running any of these commands on your dump file? If so, please share the path to your `.dmp` file and I'll help drive the analysis.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2dd5c20b-f1be-43d5-9a5a-d5a575aa639f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants help analyzing it. Let me help them with this. I don't have a specific skill for analyzing crash dumps (the `dump-collect` skill is for *collecting* dumps, not analyzing them). Let me provide guidance on how to analyze a .NET crash dump.\n\nLet me check what tools are available in the environment and what's in the current directory.","outputTokens":460,"requestId":"D800:1F45CF:D68815:F7DCC8:69F2B6AA"},"id":"7f5b9915-44e8-41ca-8034-425122eb0cdb","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:56:06.650Z","parentId":"4a63fbf6-08b6-4fe5-9485-86ca746cd6c8"}
